War between Shining Path ("Sendero Luminoso"), a Maoist guerrilla
organization whose strength was with coca-growing farmers, and Peru's
government cost 20,000 lives.  Several of the organization's leaders,
who were imprisoned, proposed surrendering weapons and receiving a
general amnesty to secure peace.  Other factions vowed to continue its
struggle.</SUM>
